I tested the test and I don't think it is helpful in its current form. I reverted the fix and the test still passes, so it is not testing the problem. I did some digging in the existing tests and came up with this:

```java
public class ProxyClassLoaderNB11PackageAnnotationsTest extends NbTestCase {

    static final String TEST_PACKAGE = "org.netbeans.pkgannottest";

    public ProxyClassLoaderNB11PackageAnnotationsTest(String name) {
        super(name);
    }

    public void testPackageAnnotation() throws Exception {
        class PCL extends ProxyClassLoader {
            final String name;
            PCL(ClassLoader[] parents, String _name) {
                super(parents, false);
                addCoveredPackages(Collections.singleton(TEST_PACKAGE));
                name = _name;
            }
            protected @Override Class doLoadClass(String pkg, String name) {
                if (name.startsWith(TEST_PACKAGE)) {
                    ByteArrayOutputStream baos = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
                    InputStream is = PCL.class.getClassLoader().getResourceAsStream(name.replace('.', '/') + ".class");
                    byte[] buf = new byte[4096];
                    int read;
                    try {
                        while ((read = is.read(buf)) != -1) {
                            baos.write(buf, 0, read);
                        }
                    } catch (IOException x) {
                        assert false : x;
                    }
                    return defineClass(name, baos.toByteArray(), 0, baos.size());
                }
                return null;
            }
            protected @Override boolean shouldDelegateResource(String pkg, ClassLoader parent) {
                return parent != null || !pkg.equals("org/netbeans/pkgannottest/");
            }



            public @Override String toString() {
                return name;
            }
        }

        final PCL pcl = new PCL(new ClassLoader[] {}, "Test");
        final Class<? extends Annotation> annotClz = (Class<? extends Annotation>) pcl.loadClass(TEST_PACKAGE + ".NB11PackageTestAnnotation");
        final Package pkg = annotClz.getPackage();
        final Object annot = pkg.getAnnotation(annotClz);
        assertTrue("Annotation not found", annot != null);
    }

}
```

The above passes with the fix and does not pass without it.

